https://github.com/Xinglab/rmats2sashimiplot

!!!Note here, --b1 or b2, use comma between replicates, no blank after comma. Otherwise, the software doesn't recognize the bam files

## Option I. type the coordinate information directly.

rmats2sashimiplot --b1 /home/xu/20220207_m28_analysis_M4RNAseq/STAR_bam_2pass/KO1_2P_Aligned.sortedByCoord.out.bam,/home/xu/20220207_m28_analysis_M4RNAseq/STAR_bam_2pass/KO2_2P_Aligned.sortedByCoord.out.bam --b2 /home/xu/20220207_m28_analysis_M4RNAseq/STAR_bam_2pass/WT1_2P_Aligned.sortedByCoord.out.bam,/home/xu/20220207_m28_analysis_M4RNAseq/STAR_bam_2pass/WT2_2P_Aligned.sortedByCoord.out.bam -c chr8:+:123295825:123296214:/home/xu/20220207_m28_analysis_M4RNAseq/sashimi/gencode.vM28.primary_assembly.annotation.gff3 -t RI --l1 KO --l2 WT --exon_s 1 --intron_s 5 -o /home/xu/20220207_m28_analysis_M4RNAseq/sashimi/RI/Cdt1 --font-size 12

